-- Chilean Stocks: Copec, Corpbanca, La Polar, Lan, Sigdo Koppers
-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 2011-12-29T20:45:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/chilean-stocks-empresas-la-polar-endesa-and-lan-airlines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Santiago.  The  Ipsa (IPSA)  index rose 0.5 percent to 4,171.95. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index gained 0.8 percent to 2,260.51.  Corpbanca (CORPBANC)   fell 1.3 percent to 6.72 pesos, its
fourth day of losses. Chile’s fifth-largest lender by assets
said Mario Chamorro resigned as chief executive officer.
Cristian Canales will fill the position on an interim basis,
Corpbanca said in a statement posted on the website of Chile’s
securities regulator.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC)   rose 0.9 percent to 6,950.9
pesos, ending a five-day losing streak. The company’s Celulosa
Arauco & Constitucion SA unit agreed to buy a wood panel plant
in Moncure, North Carolina from Uniboard USA LLC, for $56
million plus $6 million in working capital.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   fell 2.6 percent to
290.48 pesos, a record low. The department-store operator that
filed for bankruptcy this year for the second time since 1999
plans to resume issuing credit cards that may be used only in
its own stores, according to a statement posted yesterday on the
website of Chile’s securities regulator.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   added 0.6 percent to 12,211 pesos,
the most in a week. Latin America’s largest airline by market
value expects no “relevant financial effect” on consolidated
earnings from Argentine authorities’ decision to revoke its
right to fly international flights from the Aeroparque Jorge
Newberry airport in  Buenos Aires , it said in a filing posted
today on the website of Chile’s securities regulator.  Sigdo Koppers SA (SK)   fell 0.3 percent to 854.09 pesos,
its fifth day of losses. The Chilean industrial holding company
prepaid a $329 million syndicated loan it secured Oct. 14 for
the acquisition of Belgium’s Magotteaux Group, Sigdo Koppers
wrote in a statement posted on the website of Chile’s securities
regulator.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
